**[Project Results]**
 In the first half of 2025, the TTS aftersales experience saw great improvements (June vs. December):
- NPS increased by **+5.1pp;**
- Perfect resolution rate improved by **+14.3pp**;
- Aftersales success rate rose by **+3.4pp**;
- Reverse logistics success rate increased by **+19.8pp**;
- Product flow optimization led to a **6.25% reduction in buyer inquiry CPO**.
**[Collaboration Highlights]**
- **Deep research and data-driven insights:**
The user research team combined monthly external attribution data with weekly internal diagnostics to quickly identify user- and order-level experience issues. Through targeted surveys, voice-of-user collection, and detractor interviews, the team completed eight deep-dive analyses and five rounds of user surveys — gathering about 8,000 targeted responses. Product and engineering teams leveraged intelligent tools for top CPO analysis to assist in pinpointing key problems.
- **Strategy decomposition and goal setting:**
Guided by research insights, the experience operations team led the process of defining core issues, setting project objectives, and identifying nine key sub-projects with clear owners and deliverables.
- **Clear ownership and collaboration:**
	- The **user research team** focused on user experience data breakdown and in-depth issue exploration (interviews);
	- The **experience operations team** designed goals and drove user benefit coverage;
	- The **product team** was responsible for launching benefit experiments and optimizing product flows;
	- The **logistics team** improved reverse logistics capabilities (PU success rate and DO coverage) and strengthened cancellation interception capabilities.
 Each team had clear ownership, measurable goals, and aligned outcomes.
- **Continuous collaboration and optimization:**
 Regular reviews at daily, weekly, and monthly levels ensured close monitoring of core metrics and ongoing improvement. Each quarter, teams aligned on strategy and requirements, and every six months conducted comprehensive retrospectives and planning workshops to drive continuous progress.

